title: Agent template selection menu lacks pagination
---
Problem
When selecting an agent template (e.g., via --agent-name or interactive selection), the menu displays all available templates in a single unbounded list. With many templates, this becomes unwieldy and can overflow message limits or UI space, particularly in constrained channels like Teams.

Why this matters
- Users with many templates (builtins + custom) get an unusable wall of text
- Teams/Telegram channel limits may truncate the menu
- Poor UX compared to paginated alternatives (e.g., /menu handling)

Acceptance criteria
- Agent template menu pages results (e.g., 5-10 per page)
- Navigation controls (next/prev) are available where supported
- Full list remains accessible via sequential browsing
- Works across channels (Teams, Telegram, CLI)

Notes
- Related: B479 (Generalize Teams /menu through shared formatter/DSL)
- Consider reusing pagination infrastructure from /menu Adaptive Card work (P2.M4.E3.T004)